Hi Joel,

Confirming this is working as it should be on the live site.

Thank you.

Cheers,
Renee

Hi Renee, 

Confirming we have updated the quick quote on the live site. Can you try and test the form to make sure the data is coming through?
https://www.stellainsurance.com.au/quick-quote/

Hi Heath,

Thanks for the email, I've been meaning to email you to day.

I did some testing this morning and all good on our side.

Thanks,
Renee

Hi David, 

Great to hear, pending confirmation from Renee and Anita, we are on standby to replicate into the live site 29 Sept at 6pm Sydney time.

Hi Heath,

That change seems to have done the trick.

Renee, Anita, could you complete a few quick quotes too just to check that you can get an address returned and flow into Symphony ok from the Staging site.

We have updated the documentation here and this now includes an updated root URL for development and the root URL that you would need for production (this will be enabled by COP tomorrow).

We are planning on switching over on 29th at 9am UK / 6pm SYD time so it would be good to coordinate with yourselves.

Best Regards,

David

Hi Heath,

We have tested the integration and at present on staging it returns an error when trying to get a quick quote.

The team have been able to troubleshoot what the issue is. The reference needs to be read from the return value and currently it is passing AU-New South Wales, whereas it needs to pass AU-NSW. Please see attached screenshot.

Please let us know if you need any more information on how to resolve it.
